Courtesy #DStv403 KOMANI - First- it paid R15-million for a dodgy stadium to be built and now, R98-million for a 6.7 kilometer stretch of road. Residents are fed up - some are going to court but some officials at the Enoch Mgijima municipality in the Eastern Cape are still defending the tender. eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila shares more details in the video above.